abstract: The police fired tear gas and used water cannons to disperse thousands of protesters outside Indonesia’s Parliament on Tuesday, while security guards inside had to break up a fight among lawmakers debating the results of an investigation into a bank bailout.

lead_paragraph: The police fired tear gas and used water cannons to disperse thousands of protesters outside Indonesia’s Parliament on Tuesday, while security guards inside had to break up a fight among lawmakers debating the results of an investigation into a bank bailout, Peter Gelling writes in The New York Times.

headline.main: Fight Erupts Over Inquiry Into Jakarta Bank Bailout
